          "sfx": [],
          "tags": [],
          "custom": {}
        },
        {
          "name": "Lycanthropic Curse",
          "value": 0,
          "description": "When your bite inflicts Damaged stress on a non-lycanthrope mortal, spend a plot point to keep an extra effect die as a Curse of Lycanthropy complication on that mortal. The complication never goes away unless removed by holy magic. A mortal with this complication also gains the Shift Forms  SFX (as described below) and is transformed against their will every night of the full moon.",
          "traits": null,
          "sfx": [],
          "tags": [],
          "custom": {}
        },
        {
          "name": "Shift Forms",
          "value": 0,
          "description": "Spend a plot point to take on a new form and gain a related D8 asset (Hybrid Form, Shape of a Boar, etc.), then stay in that form as long as the asset lasts. When transformed against your will, gain a plot point and take a Bestial Urges complication equal to your Curse of Lycanthropy trait.",
